<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:When a response already has a Connection header, the code uses memcmp(hdr->value, "close", 5) to check whether the existing header value equals the string "close". This uses memcmp to compare a null-terminated string (the header value) against the null-terminated literal "close", which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14.
</scenario>
